<DocsLayout
  title="Agent Client Protocol"
  eyebrow="Protocols"
  description="Run gode as an ACP agent over stdio."
  prev={{ href: "/docs/tui/", title: "TUI" }}
  next={{ href: "/docs/app-server/", title: "App server" }}
>
  <p>
    <code>gode acp</code> runs gode as an
    <a href="https://agentclientprotocol.com/protocol/overview" rel="noopener">Agent Client Protocol</a>
    agent over stdio. It speaks JSON-RPC 2.0 with one JSON message per line on stdin/stdout,
    which is the transport ACP clients expect.
  </p>

  <pre><code>go run ./cmd/gode acp \
  --workspace "$PWD" \
  --data-dir "$HOME/.gode" \
  --provider openai \
  --model gpt-5.5</code></pre>

  <p>For offline testing:</p>
  <pre><code>go run ./cmd/gode acp --provider mock --auto-approve</code></pre>

  <h2>What gode advertises</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>session/new</code>, <code>session/prompt</code>, <code>session/cancel</code>, <code>session/update</code>.</li>
    <li>Optional <code>session/list</code> and <code>session/close</code>.</li>
    <li>Text and <code>resource_link</code> prompt blocks. Images, audio, and embedded resources are rejected unless those capabilities are added later.</li>
    <li>Stdio MCP servers passed in <code>session/new</code>. HTTP and SSE MCP transports are not advertised.</li>
    <li>Tool progress through <code>tool_call</code> and <code>tool_call_update</code> session updates.</li>
    <li>Permission requests through <code>session/request_permission</code> when a tool needs user approval.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Minimal client exchange</h2>

  <p>Initialize the connection:</p>
  <pre><code>{`{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"method":"initialize","params":{"protocolVersion":1,"clientInfo":{"name":"example-client","version":"0.1.0"}}}`}</code></pre>

  <p>Response:</p>
  <pre><code>{`{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"result":{
  "protocolVersion":1,
  "agentInfo":{"name":"gode","title":"Gode","version":"dev"},
  "agentCapabilities":{
    "loadSession":false,
    "mcpCapabilities":{"http":false,"sse":false},
    "promptCapabilities":{"image":false,"audio":false,"embeddedContext":false},
    "sessionCapabilities":{"list":{},"close":{}}
  },
  "authMethods":[]
}}`}</code></pre>

  <p>Create a session with an absolute working directory:</p>
  <pre><code>{`{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":2,"method":"session/new","params":{"cwd":"/absolute/path/to/workspace","mcpServers":[]}}`}</code></pre>

  <p>Send a prompt using ACP content blocks:</p>
  <pre><code>{`{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":3,"method":"session/prompt","params":{
  "sessionId":"SESSION_ID",
  "prompt":[
    {"type":"text","text":"summarize this repo"},
    {"type":"resource_link","name":"README.md","uri":"file:///absolute/path/to/workspace/README.md"}
  ]
}}`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Streaming updates</h2>
  <p>While the turn runs, gode emits <code>session/update</code> notifications:</p>
  <pre><code>{`{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"session/update","params":{
  "sessionId":"SESSION_ID",
  "update":{"sessionUpdate":"agent_message_chunk","content":{"type":"text","text":"..."}}
}}`}</code></pre>

  <p>When the turn completes, the original <code>session/prompt</code> request gets a stop reason:</p>
  <pre><code>{`{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":3,"result":{"stopReason":"end_turn"}}`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Cancellation</h2>
  <p>To cancel an active turn, send a notification:</p>
  <pre><code>{`{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"session/cancel","params":{"sessionId":"SESSION_ID"}}`}</code></pre>
  <p>The active prompt request will return:</p>
  <pre><code>{`{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":3,"result":{"stopReason":"cancelled"}}`}</code></pre>

  <h2>MCP servers in ACP</h2>
  <p>
    On <code>session/new</code> you can attach stdio MCP servers. Tools they expose are
    registered as <code>mcp.&lt;server-name&gt;.&lt;tool-name&gt;</code>:
  </p>
  <pre><code>{`{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":2,"method":"session/new","params":{
  "cwd":"/absolute/path/to/workspace",
  "mcpServers":[{
    "name":"tools",
    "command":"/absolute/path/to/mcp-server",
    "args":["--stdio"],
    "env":[{"name":"EXAMPLE","value":"1"}]
  }]
}}`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Permissions</h2>
  <p>If a tool needs approval, gode sends a request to the client:</p>
  <pre><code>{`{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":"permission-...","method":"session/request_permission","params":{
  "sessionId":"SESSION_ID",
  "toolCall":{"toolCallId":"call-1","title":"shell.exec","kind":"execute","status":"pending"},
  "options":[
    {"optionId":"allow_once","name":"Allow once","kind":"allow_once"},
    {"optionId":"reject_once","name":"Reject","kind":"reject_once"}
  ]
}}`}</code></pre>

  <p>Reply with the selected outcome:</p>
  <pre><code>{`{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":"permission-...","result":{"outcome":{"outcome":"selected","optionId":"allow_once"}}}`}</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
